The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in Correctional Services has increased by two, taking the combined number to 146 according to a statement. The Eastern Cape still has the highest number of confirmed cases for Correctional Services with 91 confirmed cases with only one recovery recorded. Thirty-five officials at the province have tested positive with 56 being inmates. In the Western Cape, there is recorded death that is still being investigated and at the head office, one official has tested positive with also one having registered as a recovered patient. Below is a graphic that shows Correctional Services COVID-19 cases:  Loadingâ€¦ (function(d){var js, id="pikto-embed-js", ref=d.getElementsByTagName("script")[0];if (d.getElementById(id)) { return;}js=d.createElement("script"); js.id=id; js.async=true;js.src="https://create.piktochart.com/assets/embedding/embed.js";ref.parentNode.insertBefore(js, ref);}(document)); 